#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_eyes.md:6
msgid "# Robe of Eyes _Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_eyes.md:8
msgid ""
"This robe is adorned with eyelike patterns. While you wear the robe, you "
"gain the following benefits:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_eyes.md:12
msgid ""
"The robe lets you see in all directions, and you have advantage on Wisdom "
"(Perception) checks that rely on sight."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_eyes.md:12
msgid "You have darkvision out to a range of 120 feet."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_eyes.md:12
msgid ""
"You can see invisible creatures and objects, as well as see into the "
"Ethereal Plane, out to a range of 120 feet."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_eyes.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The eyes on the robe can't be closed or averted. Although you can close or "
"avert your own eyes, you are never considered to be doing so while wearing "
"this robe.    \n"
"A **_light_** spell cast on the robe or a **_daylight_** spell cast within 5 "
"feet of the robe causes you to be blinded for 1 minute. At the end of each "
"of your turns, you can make a Constitution saving throw (DC 11 for "
"**_light_** or DC 15 for **_daylight_**), ending the blindness on a "
"success. \n"
msgstr ""
